HEADWORD: Retentor
<hw>Re*ten"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a
retainer.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A muscle which serves to retain
an organ or part in place, esp. when retracted. See <xex>Illust.</xex>
of <er>Phylactolemata</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

